 - top -> process view
 - iotop -> Input / output top
 - powertop -> power usage top
    - cpupower idle-info -> available idle C-states. An idle C-state is a CPU
      mode in which the cpu is sleep to reduce power consumption. There are
      several modes which have different savings and different latencies to
      exit the idle state.
    - cpupower monitor -m Idle_Stats -> show statistics per idle C-state
 - tcptrack -i <interface> -> network connection top
